  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID19 - Handwashing with Soap Trainings</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide practical hand hygiene trainings, bars of soap and zero-touch foot-operated handwashing stations (Maji bucket) in rural Ghana. The goal is to equip these communities with the knowledge and tools to shield themselves against the potential spread of COVID-19. Thus far, we have reached more than 70,000 people with hygiene essentials and trainings but we need continued support to scale up our efforts and curb the risk of an outbreak.</narrative>
  </description>
